## PWA Setup — Install to Phone, Get Notifications

This makes the web app installable on your phone home screen like a native app, with daily push notifications to do your sessions.

### Step 1 — Add `public/manifest.json`

```json
{
  "name": "Recharge",
  "short_name": "Recharge",
  "description": "Daily voice coaching for high performers",
  "start_url": "/dashboard",
  "display": "standalone",
  "background_color": "#0f0c1a",
  "theme_color": "#0f0c1a",
  "icons": [
    { "src": "/icon-192.png", "sizes": "192x192", "type": "image/png" },
    { "src": "/icon-512.png", "sizes": "512x512", "type": "image/png" }
  ]
}
```

Add `<link rel="manifest" href="/manifest.json" />` to `app/layout.tsx`.

### Step 2 — Register a service worker

Create `public/sw.js`:

```js
self.addEventListener('push', (event) => {
  const data = event.data?.json() ?? {}
  event.waitUntil(
    self.registration.showNotification(data.title || 'Recharge', {
      body: data.body || 'Your 3 daily sessions are ready.',
      icon: '/icon-192.png',
      badge: '/icon-192.png',
      data: { url: '/dashboard' }
    })
  )
})

self.addEventListener('notificationclick', (event) => {
  event.notification.close()
  event.waitUntil(clients.openWindow(event.notification.data.url))
})
```

Register it in `app/layout.tsx` or a client component:

```ts
if ('serviceWorker' in navigator) {
  navigator.serviceWorker.register('/sw.js')
}
```

### Step 3 — Push subscription in the Durable Object

When the user grants notification permission, save their Web Push subscription object to their Durable Object record. The existing DO storage pattern handles this with one new field.

```ts
// In durable-object.ts, add to user record:
pushSubscription: PushSubscription | null
notificationTime: string  // e.g. "08:00" in user's timezone
```

### Step 4 — Daily notification via Cloudflare Cron Trigger

Add to `wrangler.toml`:

```toml
[triggers]
crons = ["0 * * * *"]  // runs every hour, filter by user's preferred time
```

The Cron Worker iterates users who haven't completed today's sessions and sends a Web Push to their stored subscription using the Web Push API.

### iPhone install instructions (for you right now)

1. Open the app in Safari on your iPhone
2. Tap the Share button (box with arrow)
3. Scroll down and tap "Add to Home Screen"
4. Tap Add
5. Open the app from your home screen and grant notification permission when prompted

**Note:** On iPhone, Web Push only works for PWAs added to the home screen. It won't work from a Safari browser tab. Once installed, notifications work the same as any native app.

