## What This Is NOT

To keep the App Store path clean when the time comes:

- Do not use the word "therapy" anywhere in the app or marketing
- Do not claim to diagnose burnout
- Do not reference clinical assessment tools by name (MBI)
- The AI is a **coach**, not a therapist
- The disclaimer component should read something like: *"Recharge is a coaching tool, not a substitute for medical or mental health care. If you're experiencing a mental health crisis, please contact a professional."*

This positions it cleanly as a Lifestyle app. The science underneath is rigorous — the framing is coaching and performance recovery.

